DevOps Implementation on the go web application
The main goal of this project is to implement End-to-End DevOps practices in the Go web application.

🚀 DevOps Implementation

1. Source Code Setup
Cloned the repository and verified project structure and dependencies.

2. Application Execution
Built and ran the application locally to ensure baseline functionality before DevOps integration.

3. Containerization
Created a Dockerfile and containerized the application using Docker to ensure consistency across environments.

4. Kubernetes Manifests
Structured deployment configuration by creating a k8s/manifests directory for Kubernetes resources.

5. Cluster Provisioning
Provisioned a managed Kubernetes cluster using Amazon EKS for scalable container orchestration.

6. Ingress Configuration
Configured Ingress controller to enable external access and route traffic to services داخل the cluster.

7. Helm Integration
Created Helm charts using Helm for simplified and reusable Kubernetes deployments.

8. CI Pipeline (GitHub Actions)
Implemented Continuous Integration using GitHub Actions to automate build and container image creation.

9. CD Pipeline (GitOps with ArgoCD)
Enabled Continuous Deployment using Argo CD for automated, declarative application delivery.
